Reasoning: The paper deals with the connection between logic and automata for string transformations, which falls under the area of formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL). The use of monadic second-order logic and first-order logic also suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper also introduces a new notion of transition monoid for streaming string transducers, which involves structural properties of input automata and variable dependencies, indicating a possible connection to the sub-category of data structures (cs.DS) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper proposes a class of first-order definable transformations, which falls under the area of theoretical computer science (cs.THEORY).
